itemLabel: Ralph Grey, Baron Grey of Naunton

wikipedia_page.main: Ralph Francis Alnwick Grey, Baron Grey of Naunton,  (15 April 1910 – 17 October 1999) was the last Governor of Northern Ireland.  He was created a Life Peer as Baron Grey of Naunton, of Naunton in the County of Gloucestershire, on 17 September 1968.
